Reasoning: The paper deals with anonymous shared memory and presents an algorithm for desanonymizing it. This falls under the category of distributed computing and algorithms. The paper also mentions the use of a deadlock-free mutex algorithm, which falls under the category of concurrent data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC and cs.DS. The paper also discusses the necessary and sufficient condition on the size of the anonymous memory, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper presents a symmetric algorithm, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL).
